Script Code (wanderlust-backup.sh)
On the VM, create the script:
sudo nano /usr/local/bin/wanderlust-backup.sh

Paste this:
#!/bin/bash
# Simple backup script for WanderLust website

WEBROOT="/var/www/html"                         # Website folder
BACKUPDIR="/var/backups/wanderlust"             # Folder to store backups
LOGFILE="/var/log/wanderlust-backup.log"        # Log file to record backups

# Create backup folder if it doesn't exist
mkdir -p "$BACKUPDIR"

# Create a timestamp for the backup file
TIME=$(date +"%Y-%m-%d_%H-%M-%S")

# Create a compressed backup of the website
tar -czf "$BACKUPDIR/wanderlust_$TIME.tar.gz" "$WEBROOT"

# Log the backup action
echo "$(date) - Backup created: wanderlust_$TIME.tar.gz" >> "$LOGFILE"
Save and exit.
Make it executable and create the backup directory (first time):
sudo chmod +x /usr/local/bin/wanderlust-backup.sh
sudo mkdir -p /var/backups/wanderlust

10.3 Running and Verifying the Script
Run the script:
sudo /usr/local/bin/wanderlust-backup.sh

Check that a backup was created:
ls -lh /var/backups/wanderlust
You should see files like:
wanderlust_2025-11-14_02-30-22.tar.gz

Check the log file:
cat /var/log/wanderlust-backup.log
You should see lines like:
Fri Nov 14 02:30:22 UTC 2025 - Backup created: wanderlust_2025-11-14_02-30-22.tar.gz
(Screenshot: ls /var/backups/wanderlust and cat /var/log/wanderlust-backup.log)

This will automatically create daily backups of your website.
